- **Install StackExchange.Redis**: `dotnet add package StackExchange.Redis`
- **Latest Version**: Check [NuGet](https://www.nuget.org/packages/StackExchange.Redis/)
- **Configure IDistributedCache**:
  ```csharp
  services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(options =>
  {
      options.Configuration = "your_redis_connection_string";
      options.InstanceName = "SampleInstance";
  });
  ```
- **Access Cache in Code**:
  ```csharp
  public class MyController : Controller
  {
      private readonly IDistributedCache _cache;

      public MyController(IDistributedCache cache)
      {
          _cache = cache;
      }

      public async Task<IActionResult> Index()
      {
          var cachedValue = await _cache.GetStringAsync("myKey");
          if (cachedValue == null)
          {
              // Cache miss, fetch data and store in cache
              cachedValue = "data";
              await _cache.SetStringAsync("myKey", cachedValue);
          }
          return Content(cachedValue);
      }
  }
  ```
- **Redis Connection String**: Format `host:port` or `host:port,password=yourpassword`
- **InstanceName**: Optional, used for partitioning cache keys
- **Cache Expiration**:
  ```csharp
  await _cache.SetStringAsync("myKey", "data", new DistributedCacheEntryOptions
  {
      AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)
  });
  ```
- **Docker Setup**: Use official Redis image `docker run -d --name myredis -p 6379:6379 redis`
- **BenchmarkDotNet**: For performance testing, install and use [BenchmarkDotNet](https://github.com/dotnet/BenchmarkDotNet)
- **HybridCache Migration**: Consider migrating from in-memory to Redis for scalability.

- Install StackExchange.Redis via NuGet: `dotnet add package StackExchange.Redis`
- Use latest version of ASP.NET Core and SignalR.
- Configure Redis in `appsettings.json`:
  ```json
  "ConnectionStrings": {
    "RedisCache": "your_redis_connection_string"
  }
  ```
- Register IDistributedCache in `Startup.cs`:
  ```csharp
  services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(options =>
  {
      options.Configuration = Configuration.GetConnectionString("RedisCache");
      options.InstanceName = "SampleInstance";
  });
  ```
- Inject `IDistributedCache` into your controllers or services.
- Use Redis for caching in your application logic.
